{title:'Business Development Intern',stipend:'₹8K-40K/month + incentives',hours:'45-55 hrs/week',access:'Accessible',daily:['Research and identify 15-20 potential clients/partners weekly','Conduct outreach via email, LinkedIn, and warm introductions','Qualify leads: understand needs, budget, timeline, decision-makers','Schedule and prepare for discovery/demo meetings','Maintain CRM with accurate pipeline updates and notes','Support proposal and pitch deck preparation','Track BD metrics: outreach volume, response rate, meetings booked','Attend networking events and conferences when possible'],hard:[['Lead Research (LinkedIn, Crunchbase, databases)','Intermediate'],['CRM Management (Salesforce, HubSpot)','Intermediate'],['Cold Outreach (Email writing, LinkedIn messages)','Intermediate'],['PowerPoint (Proposals, pitch decks)','Basic'],['Excel (Pipeline tracking, analysis)','Basic'],['Video Call Tools (Zoom, Google Meet)','Basic'],['Basic Market Research','Basic']],soft:['Communication (clear, concise, professional)','Relationship building (BD is about trust, not transactions)','Persistence (most outreach gets ignored)','Curiosity (understanding prospect\'s business deeply)','Organisation (juggling multiple prospects at different stages)'],deg:'BBA, B.Com, MBA, any business degree',deg2:'ALL degrees welcome. This role rewards hustle over pedigree. B.Tech students: your structured thinking helps in qualification. Arts students: your communication skills are valuable. Show any entrepreneurial or networking experience. College sponsorships, event organising, freelancing - all count.',foru:'You enjoy meeting new people and building relationships. You\'re good at understanding what others need. You can articulate value propositions clearly. Rejection doesn\'t demotivate you. You want a role where effort directly equals results.'},
{title:'Partnerships & Alliances Intern',stipend:'₹10K-35K/month',hours:'40-50 hrs/week',access:'Moderate',daily:['Research potential partnership opportunities (co-marketing, integrations, channel)','Reach out to potential partners via email and LinkedIn','Coordinate meetings between internal teams and partner organisations','Support partnership deal structuring and documentation','Track partnership performance metrics: revenue share, leads generated','Maintain partner relationships through regular check-ins','Create partnership proposals and pitch materials','Document partnership processes and playbooks'],hard:[['Partner Research (Identifying strategic fit)','Intermediate'],['PowerPoint (Partnership proposals)','Intermediate'],['Excel (Partnership modelling, tracking)','Basic'],['Contract Basics (Understanding term sheets)','Basic'],['CRM/Partner Tracking Tools','Basic'],['Market Research','Basic'],['Basic Financial Understanding','Basic']],soft:['Strategic thinking (identifying win-win opportunities)','Relationship management (long-term partnerships over quick wins)','Negotiation (finding mutually beneficial terms)','Cross-functional coordination (working with legal, product, marketing)','Patience (partnership deals take time)'],deg:'BBA, B.Com, MBA, Economics',deg2:'Any degree with business exposure works. B.Tech students: your analytical skills help in partnership modelling. Show any experience managing external stakeholders or coordinating between organisations. More strategic than pure sales.',foru:'You think about win-win scenarios, not just closing deals. You\'re good at building long-term relationships. You can navigate complex stakeholder dynamics. You enjoy strategic planning over tactical execution. You want to work on deals that transform businesses.'}
